00:42:48.250 --> 00:42:49.250
“To that Ambika who is worthy of worship
by all Devas and sages and pervades this world

00:42:49.250 --> 00:42:50.250
by Her power and who is the embodiment of
the entire powers of all the hosts of Devas,

00:42:50.250 --> 00:42:51.250
we bow in devotion.

00:42:51.250 --> 00:42:52.250
May She grant us auspicious things!

00:42:52.250 --> 00:42:53.250
Shri Mataji: Did you hear that?

00:42:53.250 --> 00:42:54.250
“Embodiment of all the powers."

00:42:54.250 --> 00:42:55.250
Yogi continues:

00:42:55.250 --> 00:42:56.250
“May Chandika, whose incomparable greatness
and power Bhagavan Vishnu, Brahma and Hara

00:42:56.250 --> 00:42:57.250
are unable to describe, –

00:42:57.250 --> 00:42:58.250
Shri Mataji: Hara is Shiva.

00:42:58.250 --> 00:42:59.250
Yogi continues:

00:42:59.250 --> 00:43:00.250
“…bestow Her mind on protecting the entire
world and on destroying the fear of evil.

00:43:00.250 --> 00:43:01.250
“O Devi, we bow before You, who are yourself
good fortune in the dwellings of the virtuous,

00:43:01.250 --> 00:43:02.250
and ill-fortune in those of the vicious, intelligence
in the hearts of the learned, faith in the

00:43:02.250 --> 00:43:03.250
hearts of the good, and modesty in the hearts
of the high-born.

00:43:03.250 --> 00:43:04.250
May You protect the universe!

00:43:04.250 --> 00:43:05.250
Shri Mataji: This is a prayer.

00:43:05.250 --> 00:43:06.250
Yogi continues:

00:43:06.250 --> 00:43:07.250
“O Devi, how can we describe Your inconceivable
form, or Your abundant surpassing valour that

00:43:07.250 --> 00:43:08.250
destroys the asuras, or Your wonderful feats
displayed in battles among all the hosts of

00:43:08.250 --> 00:43:09.250
gods, asuras and others?

00:43:09.250 --> 00:43:10.250
“You are the origin of all the worlds!

00:43:10.250 --> 00:43:11.250
Though You are possessed of the three gunas
You are not known to have any of their attendant

00:43:11.250 --> 00:43:12.250
defects (like passion)!

00:43:12.250 --> 00:43:13.250
You are incomprehensible even to Vishnu, Siva
and others!

00:43:13.250 --> 00:43:14.250
You are the resort of all!

00:43:14.250 --> 00:43:15.250
The entire world is composed of an infinitesimal
portion of yourself!

00:43:15.250 --> 00:43:16.250
You are verily the supreme primordial Prakriti
untransformed.

00:43:16.250 --> 00:43:17.250
“O Devi, You are Svaha at whose utterance
the whole assemblage of gods attain satisfaction

00:43:17.250 --> 00:43:18.250
in all the sacrifices.

00:43:18.250 --> 00:43:19.250
You are the Svadha which gives satisfaction
to the manes.

00:43:19.250 --> 00:43:20.250
Therefore You are chanted (as Svaha and Svadha
in Sacrifices) by people.

00:43:20.250 --> 00:43:21.250
“O Devi, You are Bhagavati, the supreme
Vidya which is the cause of liberation, and

00:43:21.250 --> 00:43:22.250
great inconceivable penances (are the means
for your realization).

00:43:22.250 --> 00:43:23.250
You (the supreme knowledge) are cultivated
by sages who desire liberation, whose senses

00:43:23.250 --> 00:43:24.250
are well restrained, who are devoted to Reality,
and have shed all the blemishes.

00:43:24.250 --> 00:43:25.250
Shri Mataji: See.

00:43:25.250 --> 00:43:26.250
That’s why very few people stick on to Sahaj
Yoga.

00:43:26.250 --> 00:43:27.250
The description of sages is clear-cut.

00:43:27.250 --> 00:43:28.250
Again read it?

00:43:28.250 --> 00:43:29.250
Yogi repeats and continues:

00:43:29.250 --> 00:43:30.250
“O Devi, You are Bhagavati, the supreme
Vidya which is the cause of liberation, and

00:43:30.250 --> 00:43:31.250
great inconceivable penances (are the means
for your realization).

00:43:31.250 --> 00:43:32.250
You (the supreme knowledge) are cultivated
by sages who desire liberation, whose senses

00:43:32.250 --> 00:43:33.250
are well-restrained, -“

00:43:33.250 --> 00:43:34.250
Shri Mataji: “Senses are well restrained."

00:43:34.250 --> 00:43:35.250
Yogi:

00:43:35.250 --> 00:43:36.250
“…who are devoted to Reality,”

00:43:36.250 --> 00:43:37.250
Shri Mataji: “Who are devoted to Reality."

00:43:37.250 --> 00:43:38.250
Yogi:

00:43:38.250 --> 00:43:39.250
“…and have shed all the blemishes.

00:43:39.250 --> 00:43:40.250
“You are the soul of Sabda-Brahman.

00:43:40.250 --> 00:43:41.250
You are the repository of the very pure Ri…”

00:43:41.250 --> 00:43:42.250
Yogi gets tongue tied on the words “Rig-veda”.

00:43:42.250 --> 00:43:43.250
Shri Mataji asks: You are what?

00:43:43.250 --> 00:43:44.250
Yogi unsure: Rishis?

00:43:44.250 --> 00:43:45.250
Shri Mataji: Rishis are the people who are
saints or sages.

00:43:45.250 --> 00:43:46.250
Yogi:

00:43:46.250 --> 00:43:47.250
“You are the repository of the very pure
Rishis.

00:43:47.250 --> 00:43:48.250
sic

00:43:48.250 --> 00:43:49.250
Shri Mataji: All the sages, you see they are
repositories.

00:43:49.250 --> 00:43:50.250
Is all the sages.

00:43:50.250 --> 00:43:51.250
Yogi continues:

00:43:51.250 --> 00:43:52.250
“…and Yajus hymns, and of Samans, the
recital of whose words is beautiful

00:43:52.250 --> 00:43:53.250
Shri Mataji: These are Vedas.

00:43:53.250 --> 00:43:54.250
Yogi continues:

00:43:54.250 --> 00:43:55.250
“…with the Udgitha!

00:43:55.250 --> 00:43:56.250
You are Bhagavati embodying the three Vedas.

00:43:56.250 --> 00:43:57.250
And You are the sustenance whereby life is
maintained.

00:43:57.250 --> 00:43:58.250
You are the supreme destroyer of the pain
of all the worlds.

00:43:58.250 --> 00:43:59.250
“O Devi, You are the Intellect, by which
the essence of all the scriptures is comprehended.

00:43:59.250 --> 00:44:00.250
You are Durga, the boat that takes men across
the difficult ocean of worldly existence,

00:44:00.250 --> 00:44:01.250
devoid of attachments.

00:44:01.250 --> 00:44:02.250
You are Shri Laksmi who has invariably taken
Her abode in the heart of Vishnu.

00:44:02.250 --> 00:44:03.250
You are indeed Gauri who has established herself
with Siva.

00:44:03.250 --> 00:44:04.250
“Gently smiling, pure, resembling the full
moon’s orb, beautiful like the splendour

00:44:04.250 --> 00:44:05.250
of excellent gold was Your face!

00:44:05.250 --> 00:44:06.250
Yet it was very strange that, being swayed
by anger, Mahisasura suddenly struck Your

00:44:06.250 --> 00:44:07.250
face when he saw it.

00:44:07.250 --> 00:44:08.250
“Far stranger is it that after seeing Your
wrathful face, O Devi, terrible with its frowns

00:44:08.250 --> 00:44:09.250
and red in hue like the rising moon, that
Mahisasura did not forthwith give up his life!

00:44:09.250 --> 00:44:10.250
For, who can live after beholding the enraged
Destroyer?

00:44:10.250 --> 00:44:11.250
“O Devi, be propitious.

00:44:11.250 --> 00:44:12.250
You are Supreme.

00:44:12.250 --> 00:44:13.250
If enraged, You forthwith destroy the (asura)
families for the welfare (of the world).

00:44:13.250 --> 00:44:14.250
This was known the very moment the extensive
forces of Mahisasura were brought to their

00:44:14.250 --> 00:44:15.250
end.

00:44:15.250 --> 00:44:16.250
“You who are always bounteous, those (fortunate
ones) with whom You are well pleased, are

00:44:16.250 --> 00:44:17.250
indeed the object of esteem in the country,
theirs are riches, theirs are glories, and

00:44:17.250 --> 00:44:18.250
their acts of righteousness perish not; they
are indeed blessed and possessed of devoted

00:44:18.250 --> 00:44:19.250
children, servants and wives.

00:44:19.250 --> 00:44:20.250
“By Your grace, O Devi, the blessed individual
does daily all righteous deeds with utmost

00:44:20.250 --> 00:44:21.250
care and thereby attains to heaven.

00:44:21.250 --> 00:44:22.250
Are You not, therefore O Devi, the bestower
of reward in all the three worlds?

00:44:22.250 --> 00:44:23.250
“When called to mind in a difficult pass,
You remove fear for every person.

00:44:23.250 --> 00:44:24.250
When called to mind by those in happiness,
You bestow a mind still further pious.

00:44:24.250 --> 00:44:25.250
Which goddess but You, O Dispeller of poverty,
pain and fear, has an ever sympathetic heart

00:44:25.250 --> 00:44:26.250
for helping everyone?

00:44:26.250 --> 00:44:27.250
“The world attains happiness by the killing
of these (foes) and though these (asuras)

00:44:27.250 --> 00:44:28.250
have committed sins enough to keep them long
in hell, let them reach heaven by meeting

00:44:28.250 --> 00:44:29.250
death eventually at the battle (with me)-
thinking thus, that You, O Devi, certainly

00:44:29.250 --> 00:44:30.250
destroy our enemies.

00:44:30.250 --> 00:44:31.250
“Don’t” You reduce to ashes all asuras
by mere sight?

00:44:31.250 --> 00:44:32.250
But You direct Your weapons against them so
that even the inimical ones, purified by the

00:44:32.250 --> 00:44:33.250
missiles, may attain the higher worlds.

00:44:33.250 --> 00:44:34.250
Such is Your most kindly intention towards
them.

00:44:34.250 --> 00:44:35.250
“If the eyes of the asuras had not been
put out by the terrible flashes of the mass

00:44:35.250 --> 00:44:36.250
of light issuing from Your sword or by the
copious lustre of Your spearpoint, it is because

00:44:36.250 --> 00:44:37.250
they saw also Your face resembling the moon,
giving out (cool) rays.

00:44:37.250 --> 00:44:38.250
“O Devi, Your nature is to subdue the conduct
of the wicked; this Your peerless beauty is

00:44:38.250 --> 00:44:39.250
inconceivable for others; Your power destroys
those who have robbed the Devas of their prowess,

00:44:39.250 --> 00:44:40.250
and You have thus manifested Your compassion
even towards the enemies.

00:44:40.250 --> 00:44:41.250
“What is Your prowess to be compared to?

00:44:41.250 --> 00:44:42.250
Where can one find this beauty (of Yours)
most charming, (yet) striking fear in enemies?

00:44:42.250 --> 00:44:43.250
Compassion in heart and relentlessness in
battle are seen, O Devi, O Bestower of boons,

00:44:43.250 --> 00:44:44.250
only in You in all the three worlds!

00:44:44.250 --> 00:44:45.250
“Through the destruction of the enemies
all these three worlds have been saved by

00:44:45.250 --> 00:44:46.250
You.

00:44:46.250 --> 00:44:47.250
Having killed them in the battle-front, You
have led even those hosts of enemies to heaven,

00:44:47.250 --> 00:44:48.250
and You have dispelled our fear of the frenzied
enemies of the Devas.

00:44:48.250 --> 00:44:49.250
Salutation to You!

00:44:49.250 --> 00:44:50.250
“O Devi, protect us with Your spear.

00:44:50.250 --> 00:44:51.250
O Ambika, protect us with Your sword, protect
us by the sound of Your bell and by the twang

00:44:51.250 --> 00:44:52.250
of Your bow-string.

00:44:52.250 --> 00:44:53.250
“O Candika, guard us in the east, in the
west, in the north and in the south by the

00:44:53.250 --> 00:44:54.250
brandishing of Your spear.

00:44:54.250 --> 00:44:55.250
O Iswari!

00:44:55.250 --> 00:44:56.250
“Protect us and the earth with those lovely
forms of Yours moving about in the three worlds,

00:44:56.250 --> 00:44:57.250
as also with Your exceedingly terrible forms.

00:44:57.250 --> 00:44:58.250
“O Ambika, protect us on every side with
Your sword, spear and club and whatever other

00:44:58.250 --> 00:44:58.257
weapons Your sprite-like (soft) hand has touched."
